Initial version of the MIB module.

cospf.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W. Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-ospf@cisco.com
cospf.description: An extension to the MIB module defined in RFC 1850 for managing OSPF implimentation. Most of the MIB definitions are based on the IETF draft < draft-ietf-ospf-mib-update-05.txt > . Support for OSPF Sham link is also added

cospfRFC1583Compatibility.name: cospfRFC1583Compatibility
cospfRFC1583Compatibility.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 16.4.1 External path preferences
cospfRFC1583Compatibility.description: Indicates metrics used to choose among multiple AS- external-LSAs. When cospfRFC1583Compatibility is set to enabled, only cost will be used when choosing among multiple AS-external-LSAs advertising the same destination. When cospfRFC1583Compatibility is set to disabled, preference will be driven first by type of path using cost only to break ties.

cospfOpaqueLsaSupport.name: cospfOpaqueLsaSupport
cospfOpaqueLsaSupport.description: The router's support for Opaque LSA types.

cospfTrafficEngineeringSupport.name: cospfTrafficEngineeringSupport
cospfTrafficEngineeringSupport.description: The router's support for OSPF traffic engineering.

cospfOpaqueASLsaCount.name: cospfOpaqueASLsaCount
cospfOpaqueASLsaCount.description: The total number of Opaque AS link-state advertisements in the link state database.

cospfOpaqueASLsaCksumSum.name: cospfOpaqueASLsaCksumSum
cospfOpaqueASLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the Opaque AS link-state advertisements' LS checksums contained link state database.

cospfAreaTable.name: cospfAreaTable
cospfAreaTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 6 The Area Data Structure
cospfAreaTable.description: Information describing the configured parameters and cumulative statistics of the router's attached areas.

cospfAreaEntry.name: cospfAreaEntry
cospfAreaEntry.description: Information describing the configured parameters and cumulative statistics of one of the router's attached areas.

cospfOpaqueAreaLsaCount.name: cospfOpaqueAreaLsaCount
cospfOpaqueAreaLsaCount.description: The total number of Opaque Area and AS link-state advertisements in the link state database of this area.

cospfOpaqueAreaLsaCksumSum.name: cospfOpaqueAreaLsaCksumSum
cospfOpaqueAreaLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the Opaque Area and AS link-state advertisements' LS checksums contained link state database of this area. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in the link state database for Opaque Area and AS link-state advertisements

cospfAreaNssaTranslatorRole.name: cospfAreaNssaTranslatorRole
cospfAreaNssaTranslatorRole.description: Indicates an NSSA Border router's ability to perform NSSA translation of type-7 LSAs into type-5 LSAs.

cospfAreaNssaTranslatorState.name: cospfAreaNssaTranslatorState
cospfAreaNssaTranslatorState.description: Indicates if and how an NSSA Border router is performing NSSA translation of type-7 LSAs into type-5 LSAs. When this object set to enabled, the NSSA Border router's cospfAreaNssaExtTranslatorRole has been set to always. When this object is set to elected, a candidate NSSA Border router is Translating type-7 LSAs into type-5. When this object is set to disabled, a candidate NSSA Border router is NOT translating type-7 LSAs into type-5.

cospfAreaNssaTranslatorEvents.name: cospfAreaNssaTranslatorEvents
cospfAreaNssaTranslatorEvents.description: Indicates the number of Translator State changes that have occurred since the last boot-up.

cospfLsdbTable.name: cospfLsdbTable
cospfLsdbTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12 Link State Advertisements
cospfLsdbTable.description: The OSPF Process's Link State Database. This table is meant for Opaque LSA's

cospfLsdbType.name: cospfLsdbType
cospfLsdbType.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix A.4.1 The Link State Advertisement header The OSPF Opaque LSA Option (RFC 2370)
cospfLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format.

cospfLsdbSequence.name: cospfLsdbSequence
cospfLsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6 LS sequence number
cospfLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.

cospfLsdbAge.name: cospfLsdbAge
cospfLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.

cospfLsdbChecksum.name: cospfLsdbChecksum
cospfLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

cospfLsdbAdvertisement.name: cospfLsdbAdvertisement
cospfLsdbAdvertisement.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12 Link State Adverisements
cospfLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire Link State Advertisement, including its header.

cospfIfTable.name: cospfIfTable
cospfIfTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.3 Router interface parameters
cospfIfTable.description: The OSPF Interface Table describes the inter- faces from the viewpoint of OSPF.

cospfIfEntry.name: cospfIfEntry
cospfIfEntry.description: The OSPF Interface Entry describes one inter- face from the viewpoint of OSPF.

cospfIfLsaCount.name: cospfIfLsaCount
cospfIfLsaCount.description: The total number of link-local link state advertisements in this interface's link-local link state database.

cospfIfLsaCksumSum.name: cospfIfLsaCksumSum
cospfIfLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the link-state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this interface's link-local link state database. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in the interface's link state database, and to compare the interface link-state database of routers attached to the same subnet.

cospfVirtIfTable.name: cospfVirtIfTable
cospfVirtIfTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.4 Virtual link parameters
cospfVirtIfTable.description: Information about this router's virtual inter- faces.

cospfVirtIfEntry.name: cospfVirtIfEntry
cospfVirtIfEntry.description: Information about a single Virtual Interface.

cospfVirtIfLsaCount.name: cospfVirtIfLsaCount
cospfVirtIfLsaCount.description: The total number of link-local link state advertisements in this virtual interface's link-local link state database.

cospfVirtIfLsaCksumSum.name: cospfVirtIfLsaCksumSum
cospfVirtIfLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the link-state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this virtual interface's link-local link state database. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in the virtual interface's link state database, and to compare the virtual interface link-state database of the virtual neighbors.

cospfShamLinkTable.name: cospfShamLinkTable
cospfShamLinkTable.description: Information about this router's sham links

cospfShamLinkEntry.name: cospfShamLinkEntry
cospfShamLinkEntry.description: Information about a single sham link

cospfShamLinkAreaId.name: cospfShamLinkAreaId
cospfShamLinkAreaId.description: The Transit Area that the Virtual Link traverses. By definition, this is not 0.0.0.0

cospfShamLinkLocalIpAddress.name: cospfShamLinkLocalIpAddress
cospfShamLinkLocalIpAddress.description: The Local IP address of the sham link.

cospfShamLinkNeighborId.name: cospfShamLinkNeighborId
cospfShamLinkNeighborId.description: The Router ID of the other end router of the sham link.

cospfShamLinkRetransInterval.name: cospfShamLinkRetransInterval
cospfShamLinkRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link-state advertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this link. This value is also used when retransmitting database description and link-state request packets. This value should be well over the expected round trip time.

cospfShamLinkHelloInterval.name: cospfShamLinkHelloInterval
cospfShamLinkHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the sham link.

cospfShamLinkRtrDeadInterval.name: cospfShamLinkRtrDeadInterval
cospfShamLinkRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neighbors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval.

cospfShamLinkEvents.name: cospfShamLinkEvents
cospfShamLinkEvents.description: The number of state changes or error events on this sham link

cospfShamLinksTable.name: cospfShamLinksTable
cospfShamLinksTable.description: Information about this router's sham links.

cospfShamLinksEntry.name: cospfShamLinksEntry
cospfShamLinksEntry.description: Information about a single sham link.

cospfShamLinksAreaId.name: cospfShamLinksAreaId
cospfShamLinksAreaId.description: The area that this sham link is part of.

cospfShamLinksLocalIpAddrType.name: cospfShamLinksLocalIpAddrType
cospfShamLinksLocalIpAddrType.description: The type of internet address of this sham link's local IP address.

cospfShamLinksLocalIpAddr.name: cospfShamLinksLocalIpAddr
cospfShamLinksLocalIpAddr.description: The Local IP address of the sham link.

cospfShamLinksRemoteIpAddrType.name: cospfShamLinksRemoteIpAddrType
cospfShamLinksRemoteIpAddrType.description: The type of internet address of this sham link's remote IP address.

cospfShamLinksRemoteIpAddr.name: cospfShamLinksRemoteIpAddr
cospfShamLinksRemoteIpAddr.description: The IP address of the other end router of the sham link.

cospfShamLinksRetransInterval.name: cospfShamLinksRetransInterval
cospfShamLinksRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link-state advertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this link. This value is also used when retransmitting database description and link-state request packets. This value should be well over the expected round trip time.

cospfShamLinksHelloInterval.name: cospfShamLinksHelloInterval
cospfShamLinksHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the sham link.

cospfShamLinksRtrDeadInterval.name: cospfShamLinksRtrDeadInterval
cospfShamLinksRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neighbors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval.

cospfShamLinksEvents.name: cospfShamLinksEvents
cospfShamLinksEvents.description: The number of state changes or error events on this sham link

cospfShamLinkNbrTable.name: cospfShamLinkNbrTable
cospfShamLinkNbrTable.description: A table of sham link neighbor information.

cospfShamLinkNbrArea.name: cospfShamLinkNbrArea
cospfShamLinkNbrArea.description: The area to which the sham link is part of.

cospfShamLinkNbrIpAddrType.name: cospfShamLinkNbrIpAddrType
cospfShamLinkNbrIpAddrType.description: The type of internet address of this sham link neighbor's IP address.

cospfShamLinkNbrIpAddr.name: cospfShamLinkNbrIpAddr
cospfShamLinkNbrIpAddr.description: The IP address this sham link neighbor is using.

cospfShamLinkNbrRtrId.name: cospfShamLinkNbrRtrId
cospfShamLinkNbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the neighboring router.

cospfShamLinkNbrOptions.name: cospfShamLinkNbrOptions
cospfShamLinkNbrOptions.description: A Bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's options field. Bit 1, if set, indicates that the system will operate on Type of Service metrics other than TOS 0. If zero, the neighbor will ignore all metrics except the TOS 0 metric. Bit 2, if set, indicates that the system is Network Multicast capable; ie, that it implements OSPF Multicast Routing.

cospfShamLinkNbrState.name: cospfShamLinkNbrState
cospfShamLinkNbrState.description: The state of this sham link neighbor relation- ship.

cospfShamLinkNbrEvents.name: cospfShamLinkNbrEvents
cospfShamLinkNbrEvents.description: The number of times this sham link has changed state or an error has occurred.

cospfShamLinkNbrLsRetransQLen.name: cospfShamLinkNbrLsRetransQLen
cospfShamLinkNbrLsRetransQLen.description: The current length of the retransmission queue. The retransmission queue is maintained for LSAs that have been flooded but not acknowledged on this adjacency.

cospfShamLinkNbrHelloSuppressed.name: cospfShamLinkNbrHelloSuppressed
cospfShamLinkNbrHelloSuppressed.description: Indicates whether Hellos are being suppressed to the neighbor.

cospfLocalLsdbTable.name: cospfLocalLsdbTable
cospfLocalLsdbTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12 Link State Advertisements and The OSPF Opaque LSA Option
cospfLocalLsdbTable.description: The OSPF Process's Link-Local Link State Database for non-virtual links.

cospfLocalLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing a 32 bit identifier in IP address format; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

cospfLocalLsdbRouterId.description: The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.
